com.swarmconnect.delegates

Interface SwarmLoginListener


  • public interface SwarmLoginListener

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void loginCanceled()
      This method is called if the user intentionally cancels logging in.
      void loginStarted()
      This method is called when the login process has started (when a login dialog is displayed to the user).
      void userLoggedIn(SwarmActiveUser user)
      This method is called when the user has successfully logged in.
      void userLoggedOut()
      This method is called when the user logs out for any reason.

    • Method Detail

      • loginStarted

        void loginStarted()
        This method is called when the login process has started (when a login dialog is displayed to the user). This will be followed by a call to either loginCanceled() or userLoggedIn(SwarmActiveUser user).

      • loginCanceled

        void loginCanceled()
        This method is called if the user intentionally cancels logging in.

      • userLoggedIn

        void userLoggedIn(SwarmActiveUser user)
        This method is called when the user has successfully logged in.
        Parameters:
        user - The SwarmActiveUser that has successfully logged in (this will match Swarm.user).

      • userLoggedOut

        void userLoggedOut()
        This method is called when the user logs out for any reason.
